w.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-9784']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-9783 - Quest NetVault Backup NVBURemovableMedia SQL Injection Remote Code Execution Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 24 Jun 2026 23:14:39 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-9783', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Quest NetVault Backup NVBURemovableMedia SQL Injection Remote Code Execution Vulnerability. This vulnerability allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code on affected installations of Quest NetVault Backup. Although authentication is required to exploit this vulnerability, the existing authentication mechanism can be bypassed. The specific flaw exists within the processing of NVBURemovableMedia JSON-RPC messages. The issue results from the lack of proper validation of a user-supplied string before using it to construct SQL queries. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to execute code in the context of NETWORK SERVICE. Was ZDI-CAN-27632.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-9783vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-9783']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-397: X.Org Server CreateSaverWindow Use-After-Free Information Disclosure Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-397/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows local attackers to disclose sensitive information on affected installations of X.Org Server. An attacker must first obtain the ability to execute low-privileged code on the target system in order to exploit this vulnerability.', 'The specific flaw exists within the handling of ScreenSaverScreenPrivateRec objects. The issue results from the lack of validating the existence of an object prior to performing operations on the object. An attacker can leverage this in conjunction with other vulnerabilities to execute arbitrary code in the context of root.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['x.org'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['ecc634f1b2f7aa473d3a267eada98c4918bf9e05']}], 'url': ['https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/xorg/xserver/-/commit/ecc634f1b2f7aa473d3a267eada98c4918bf9e05'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-50263']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-396: X.Org Server ChangeDrawableAttributes Out-Of-Bounds Read Information Disclosure Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-396/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows local attackers to disclose sensitive information on affected installations of X.Org Server. An attacker must first obtain the ability to execute low-privileged code on the target system in order to exploit this vulnerability.', 'The specific flaw exists within the handling of the numAttribs field. The issue results from the lack of proper validation of user-supplied data, which can result in a read past the end of an allocated data structure. An attacker can leverage this in conjunction with other vulnerabilities to execute arbitrary code in the context of root.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['x.org'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['6d459e4daf715bea8abdafa8fb130be2f8a1d145']}], 'url': ['https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/xorg/xserver/-/commit/6d459e4daf715bea8abdafa8fb130be2f8a1d145'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-50262']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-395: X.Org Server SyncChangeCounter Use-After-Free Privilege Escalation Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-395/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows local attackers to escalate privileges on affected installations of X.Org Server. An attacker must first obtain the ability to execute low-privileged code on the target system in order to exploit this vulnerability.', 'The specific flaw exists within the handling of SyncAwait objects. The issue results from the lack of validating the existence of an object prior to performing operations on the object. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to escalate privileges and execute arbitrary code in the context of root.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['x.org'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['bdd7bf57af208b1ddf57d4683d67104443b44812']}], 'url': ['https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/xorg/xserver/-/commit/bdd7bf57af208b1ddf57d4683d67104443b44812'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-50261']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-394: X.Org Server FreeCounter Use-After-Free Privilege Escalation Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-394/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows local attackers to escalate privileges on affected installations of X.Org Server. An attacker must first obtain the ability to execute low-privileged code on the target system in order to exploit this vulnerability.', 'The specific flaw exists within the handling of SyncAwait objects. The issue results from the lack of validating the existence of an object prior to performing operations on the object. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to escalate privileges and execute arbitrary code in the context of root.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['x.org'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['f5abfb61994471023d8c6470428c8e30c411cc0b']}], 'url': ['https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/xorg/xserver/-/commit/f5abfb61994471023d8c6470428c8e30c411cc0b'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-50260']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-393: X.Org Server SetMap Request Stack-based Buffer Overflow Privilege Escalation Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-393/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows local attackers to escalate privileges on affected installations of X.Org Server. An attacker must first obtain the ability to execute low-privileged code on the target system in order to exploit this vulnerability.', 'The specific flaw exists within the _XkbSetMapChecks function. The issue results from the lack of proper validation of the length of user-supplied data prior to copying it to a fixed-length stack-based buffer. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to escalate privileges and execute arbitrary code in the context of root.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['x.org'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['867b59b33bee669cb412f1314e47c52eacf6e00b']}], 'url': ['https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/xorg/xserver/-/commit/867b59b33bee669cb412f1314e47c52eacf6e00b'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-50259']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-392: X.Org Server Xkb Key Types Stack-based Buffer Overflow Privilege Escalation Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-392/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows local attackers to escalate privileges on affected installations of X.Org Server. An attacker must first obtain the ability to execute low-privileged code on the target system in order to exploit this vulnerability.', 'The specific flaw exists within the num_levels field. The issue results from the lack of proper validation of the length of user-supplied data prior to copying it to a fixed-length stack-based buffer. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to escalate privileges and execute arbitrary code in the context of root.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['x.org'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['543e108516428fc8c3bea91d6563ad266f9a801e']}], 'url': ['https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/xorg/xserver/-/commit/543e108516428fc8c3bea91d6563ad266f9a801e'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-50258']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-391: X.Org Server miSyncDestroyFence Use-After-Free Privilege Escalation Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-391/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows local attackers to escalate privileges on affected installations of X.Org Server. An attacker must first obtain the ability to execute low-privileged code on the target system in order to exploit this vulnerability.', 'The specific flaw exists within the handling of SyncAwait objects. The issue results from the lack of validating the existence of an object prior to performing operations on the object. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to escalate privileges and execute arbitrary code in the context of root.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['x.org'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['f5abfb61994471023d8c6470428c8e30c411cc0b']}], 'url': ['https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/xorg/xserver/-/commit/f5abfb61994471023d8c6470428c8e30c411cc0b'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-50257']}}, {'title': 'Multiples vulnérabilités dans Tenable Identity Exposure (24 juin 2026)', 'publication_date': 'Wed, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000', 'source': 'https://www.cert.ssi.gouv.fr/avis/CERTFR-2026-AVI-0796/', 'source_type': "['operational', 'vulnerabilities']", 'source_level': 1, 'text': ["De multiples vul